title: Rollercoaster boost for Dutch theme park
text:
Save 
Dutch theme park Efteling has opened a new €18 million ride. 
The park in Kaatsheuvel has unveiled the Baron 1898 rollercoaster which involves a free-fall down a mineshaft at speeds of up to 90 kilometres per hour. 
Baron 1898 is the park’s sixth rollercoaster and took 10 months to build. The ride is described as “only the ninth divecoaster worldwide”. 
Efteling’s chief executive Fons Jurgens said: “Baron 1898 is a unique and exciting addition to our existing range of attractions and one which justifiably fills me with great pride.”
